column5: Hi, I was just going through some old photos and came across this. I can't say exactly where it is as it was several years ago and I didn't drive there but it is somewhere on the southern edge of Algonquin Park near Maynooth. There is a fish in the bottom left-hand corner, possibly two, and I'd like to know what it is, however can't find it in online searches (unless it's just a very distorted catfish). Does anyone have any ideas please?
You sure of the location ? looks like Okanagan Lake to me,

I'm not so sure we're even talking about a fish let alone which species. There are at least 5 other dark wave areas on that picture that are all the same size and running the same direction as this "fish". I vote simple wave action.
Dave524 - wrong province. SingingDog - wrong continent. To GrimsbyLander - you may have a point, I think I've been looking at it for too long!  	Thanks all
Really surprised you couldn't find that in a Google search ?
Me as well-sure looks like Lake Okanogan-will we ever know?-jk  Paul
that's a pic from a "I hope to catch a fish day but I didn't so here's what I've got"  and yes I've been there.  We call them Sunset pic's...
Bootis Lacemupis. Common in Hamilton Bay of the cementitious variety.
Definitely not the Okanagan. This I know because I've never been there. Definitely a Sunset pic!
OK, a few more clues for this guessing game, Fiona!!?
